The paper proposes a new framework for hyperspectral image classification using deep learning, specifically the autoencoder model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves feature extraction and classification, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of autoencoders implies that the paper may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
